comments: Abolished 1.4.1967 and added to the parish of Clee St. Margaret.

Abolished 1.4.1987 and divided between the parishes of Craven 
    Arms, Sibdon Carwood and Wistanstow.

Abolished 1.4.1967 and divided between the parishes of Tugford 
    and Munslow. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (c).

On 30.9.1885 the part in Shropshire was transfererd to Herefordshire and 
    the parish now wholly in Herefordshire was renamed to become the parish of 
    Leintwardine.

On 30.9.1895 the part in Herefordshire was transferred to Shropshire, 
    so that thereafter Ludford was entirely in Shropshire. See also Table 2, note (k).
Abolished 9.11.1901 and added to the parish of Ludlow.

On 1.4.1889 the parts in Herefordshire and Shropshire became 
    separate parishes. See also Table 2, notes (d) and (k).

Abolished 1.4.1987 and added to the parish of Craven 
    Arms.

Abolished 1.4.1987 and added to the parish of Abdon & 
    Heath.
